=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Prepare the aryl-acid branch as methyl 2-chloro-5-fluoro-4-hydroxybenzoate (or make it from 2-chloro-5-fluoro-4-hydroxybenzoic acid by MeOH/HCl esterification). | Step 2: In parallel, start from 2-cyclopropyl-3,5-dihalopyridine and selectively displace the more activated 3-halogen with 1,1-difluoroethanol under basic SNAr conditions (e.g., NaH or Cs2CO3, DMF) to give 2-cyclopropyl-3-(1,1-difluoroethoxy)-5-halopyridine. | Step 3: Form the biaryl ether by reacting methyl 2-chloro-5-fluoro-4-hydroxybenzoate with 2-cyclopropyl-3-(1,1-difluoroethoxy)-5-halopyridine under SNAr conditions (generate the phenoxide with Cs2CO3 or K2CO3 in a polar aprotic solvent, heat) to obtain methyl 2-chloro-5-fluoro-4-((2-cyclopropyl-3-(1,1-difluoroethoxy)pyridin-5-yl)oxy)benzoate. | Step 4: Hydrolyze the methyl ester (LiOH, NaOH, or KOH in THF/MeOH/H2O), then acidify to furnish the target CC(F)(F)Oc1cc(Oc2cc(F)c(C(=O)O)cc2Cl)cnc1C1CC1.

